	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64466223"><p><div class="quote"><p>We do need to test the tech, but we shouldn't be implementing it at scale yet. We release carbon to extract stored chemical energy. That energy must be returned to sequester carbon.</p> </div><p>In this case, no.  The carbon dioxide isn't reduced (CO2 --&gt; C + O2). Instead the carbon dioxide is converted into carbonate rocks (e.g., CO2+CaO --&gt; CaCO3).</p></div>
