		<div id="comment_body_64466545"><blockquote><div><p>The math is irrefutable</p></div><span class="substr"> </span></blockquote><p>Your understanding of what's happening is not.</p><p>Deep buried rocks are not in some minimum energy state with respect to the atmosphere.  As you can readily see from the rapid chemical changes that happen to lava flows when exposed to the atmosphere - most visibly, the oxidation of FeO to Fe2O3.  Not only is deep buried rock not exposed to the atmosphere, but the thermodynamic equlibria are also different under their different temperatures and pressures.  In said rocks, calcium and magne</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64466545">

</div>
